(58, 3, '2011-05-17 01:22:45', '2011-05-17 07:22:45', 'I know you love your shiny new Android phone, or your overpowered  Android tablet... The wow factor and reactions in your friends faces are  payback enough for all the big bucks you paid for it. But over all, you  feel free! you have abandoned Steve Jobs gated gardens, you are no  longer subject to the wishes and desires of this evil empire... you`re  as free as it can gets with an open source operating system... and best  of all... your device is rated as being the top notch in technologhy...  your screen resolution doubles the retina display found in iPhones (And  rumored to be on the next iPad), each core in your quad processor is a  gazillion times faster that the fastest iPhone, you have 4G, wi-fi, USB  ports, SD slots, qwerty keyboard, GPS, compass, gyroscope, and god`s  speed dial..... but... what for? After all you`re just an user aren`t  you?\r\n\r\nLet`s emotionaly deatach ourselves from any OS or brand here to  think as the different players involved in your mobile experience....\r\n<h2>First as a developer</h2>\r\nA  closed system in a limited product line (iOS, in iPhone, iPad and iPod  Touch) offers a limited set of variables to play with... you know  exactly what is in your target market`s hands... and even the App store  offers the segmentation to distribute your application to a limited set  of devices based on the target capabilities (iPad only / iPad/iPhone for  liquid layouts, or iPhone only [BTW I hate those apps in my iPad])...  In the other hand we have a free world of wildness... and as a  developer... trust me... I`m not thinking about your fancy device! If  you`re reading this, there is a high probability that you`re a hardcore  geek equipped with the latest and most powerful device... but guess  what? You`re at the top level of the tech-chain... there is only a small  percentage of people like you... the big majority... and a lot of them  with lots of cash will want my App on their ancient 10 months old  smart-phone they just use for occasinal gaming and texting. some of this  devices will have resolutions as low as 320x240, very slow processors,  almost no memory, slow graphics, and Alzaimer`s RAM. So... I`ll probably  base my App targeting the MINIMUM COMMON DENOMINATOR to the wide  spectrum of Androids out there... and the minimum can be really low!  (Try the Eken M001 as an instance). So putting my app in the Android  Marketplace will make it available to a broad spectrum market... If I`m  targeting a specific device I shall use the manufacturer`s app  distribution solution... BTW I have seen this `Android Marketplace  alternative` for Sony, HTC, Samsung and others... but then... none of  this brands by itself reaches  a market as massive as the App Store....\r\n<h2>As  a manufacterer</h2>\r\nDo you think the manufacturing world is ruled only by  the satisfaction of consumer happiness? I`m sorry to disapoint you...  but it`s actually ruled by money... and while Apple is consolidated,  independent manufacterers are fighting to be the next market boom. (How  many times have you seen the `iphone killer` being forgotten, because  the new iphone killer is better?... Logic says that the new kid in the  block should be the iPhone killer`s killer.... but no... it`s still the  iPhone killer! so...???). Well... many companies have good ethics....  while some others will find `open source` to be the equivalent to `free`  as in `i don`t have to pay a dime to put a trendy OS in my piece-o-craB  device and print a big Android in the box.... people love Android after  all`. Some serious companies know that.... so... they want to  differentiate themselves by customizing the OS to the point where it`s  almost unrecognizable! As part of this differentiator, they even make  their own app front store to distribute content for their unique  features....(TouchFlo,'' etc...) by doing so... they are isolating  themselves to the mass market our poor confused developer portraited  above is trying to reach....\r\n<h2>As a regular user (Not a hardcore  geek)</h2>\r\nCustomization is cool... but not to the point where your  options include 16745 applications to change backgrounds, 6743 to track  your memory usage (you`d be surprised to know that the majority of the  people don`t even realize their phones have a memory). 887745 apps to  hack the kernel, and even some old school folks in WM tweaking the  registry! While the app you`re looking for is buried pages and pages  underneath those customizatrion demons.\r\n\r\nI know that the geek in you  is screaming THIS GUY IS SOO WRONG! Well... if you enjoy tweaking your  hardware to get 300fps on a game even knowing that 300fps is not  noticable by human eyes... because THAT is the fun part of the game....  more than the game itself... then think twice! Customization is your  thing... but you`re a small portion of the mass market....\r\n\r\nSo...  am I an iOS fanboy? Not at all... I had big hopes on the Nexus phone as a  google plattform distributed, manufactered and kept under certain  standards... But tose standards went to zero in a heartbeat by releasing  the OS... If things continue so in the wild... the next iPhone killer  will certainly come out of Coupertino....', 'Your Shiny New Android', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'your-shiny-new-android', '', '', '2011-05-17 01:25:01', '2011-05-17 07:25:01', '', 0, 'http://localhost/Geeksomnio-WP-theme/?p=58', 0, 'post', '', 0),
