n the top, but if you logged in you will get a page with your user name on the top that will be cached for the next time you access it.\n\nNow you need to tell your Grails application to use this new class you created and to do it you just need to set the keyGenerator attribute of the springcacheFilter, you can do this via the Config.groovy, like this:\n<pre lang="java">beans {\n  springcacheFilter {\n    keyGenerator = new MimeTypeAndAuthenticationAwareKeyGenerator()\n  }\n}</pre>', 'Grails con seguridad usando Spring Cache: Almacenando contenido por usuario', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '89-revision', '', '', '2011-05-18 21:26:32', '2011-05-19 03:26:32', '', 89, 'http://localhost/Geeksomnio-WP-theme/2011/05/18/89-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(91, 3, '2011-05-18 21:31:59', '2011-05-19 03:31:59', 'Yes.... I have a Motorola Xoom Tablet and yesterday I had my honeymoon with honeycomb... How do I feel the morning after?\r\nWell.... first of all I feel that terrible sense of guilt typical of a  hangover for having spent that huge amount of money in a tablet... and  so far... A little frustrated... The first awkward experience was the  process of buying it... I remember ordering my 3G iPad from the apple  store... It was a no-brainer... When the package arrived, I just  unpacked... Turned it on, a dialog asked me if I wanted the limited 250  Megs or the unlimited AT&amp;T package.... (yes they had unlimited back  then). Gave them my credit card.... and all set in seconds! After that I  went back to Costa Rica, performed a little surgical mod to my Kolbi  SIM (Costa Rican provider) and all set! 3G in Costa Rica.....\r\n\r\nNow on the other hand... I got the unlocked version of the Xoom, as my  visits to the US are erratical, and the main usage for this device will  be in Costa Rica... and even being unlocked, I had to get a 1 month  subscription with Verizon.... well I guess it doesn''t really matters as I  was paying extra-bucks on the already overpriced device, plus the 1  month subscription.... But guess what? It DOES matters, as I was asked  for my US Social Security number AND my US Drivers License... Well I  have neither of those as I''m a Tourist in the US! A friend helped me to  get it, but anyway.... it took the Shop employee like 30 minutes to  process my request and setup the Verizon network on my device.... HE  opened the box, HE touched my virginal device before me! He went through  the welcome process! I guess he was just being kind... anyway...  sleeker setup on the iPad, that''s for sure.....\r\n\r\nThe first few steps (literally, as I wasn''t even out of the store) was  downloading and installing skype... A bit confusing for an iOS guy... I  didn''t knew if the App was being downloaded, where I was supposed to  open it or anything.... but I guess it will take me some time to  adjust.... Less than 2 minutes after I got my first skype call... My 4  years old daughter wanted to show me a drawing she made in the  Kindergarden... but guess what? I wasn''t able to RECEIVE video from her!  And if I wasn''t able to GET video... you can correctly guess that the 5  Megapixels camera in the back or my shiny front camera were nothing  more than useless! I asked her to hold... turned on the iPad, connected  to skype, she called me again... and this time she couldn''t see me, as  there is no cameras on the iPad... but I got to see her pretty drawing  at least! Do I have to describe how frustrated I was having to go back  to my cheap (compared to the Xoom, but not cheap in any way) iPad to do  something?\r\n\r\nThen I started looking for a way to have a video call... and playing  around with the camera I opened up the camera App.... Well I haven''t  figured out how to close it...\r\n\r\nThe Verizon and Motorola logos on to, as well as the front camera  clearly suggest that the manufacturer built this device to be used  Landscape mainly but many Applications (Skype/Facebook) force the  portrait mode in some of their screens.... Also I found a very nice  little button ergonomically placed on the back right where my left index  finger is (left handed designer???). I would have thought that this  button would do something like the iPad''s front button... take me to the  main screen or close the current app.... but no... that''s the  power/sleep button.... so the only ergonomic physical contact I have  with my device is to put it away... no sense!\r\n\r\nThen I have inserted my telephone''s 8GB-music loaded micro-SD... and  nothing happened... no indication... nothing! And nothing shows me it is  there! My music is not showing and it seems like it is broken! Do I  have to go back to the store to have it replaced or am I missing  something?\r\nThere is a SIM card slot.... with a nice transparent fake sim on it  saying: "Don''t use before activating 4G" or something similar, I don''t  remember and already dumped the card) which is OVERLY confusing! What is  that supposed to mean? The 3G network is working fine in Marin  County... I guess I''ll have to go SF Downtown to get 4G... but it is  working with no SIM card on it! So... how come is this the unlocked  version? What is that SIM card slot used for? Will it work with my Costa  Rican SIM? I''ll have to wait to go back to CR to verify... so far look  scary and confusing.\r\n\r\nBut maybe the most frustrating part is the hundreds of dollars of Apps I  have on my iPad are there on the  Android Marketplace... same App, same  developers, same sellers, same price.... but I''m supposed to buy them  again to get them on Android... don''t expect a major migration from iPad  to Android if people can at least get a radical discount for apps they  already own in a different platform!\r\n\r\nSo... all in all at least I have Flash right? WRONG! Adobe''s Flash  player welcomes my Honeycomb experience with a shiny: There is no Flash  Player for your current OS Version (Honeycomb 3.0).\r\n\r\nI feel like Britney Spears drunk getting married in Vegas! My Honeymoon  with Honeycomb was not that good as my first night with the iPad... but  well I guess true love means aging together while maturing and getting  to know each other on time.... Android seems like the promise of true  love, and makes the iPad look like a spoiled gorgeous primma donna which  had me hypnotized with her enchants for the last year.\r\n\r\nTime to grow up!', 'Mi luna de miel con Honeycomb', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'mi-luna-de-miel-con-honeycomb', '', '', '2011-05-19 21:12:43', '2011-05-20 03:12:43', '', 0, 'http://localhost/Geeksomnio-WP-theme/?p=91', 0, 'post', '', 0),
